==Italian==
===Saying===
'''che sarà sarà'''
# "What will be, will be."

This old Italian saying was featured in the movie "The Barefoot Contessa", which inspired the songwriters Jay Livingston and Ray Evans to use it as a song title -- recast as "Spanish" -- when they wrote their 1956 song "Qué será será" (sung by Doris Day in Alfred Hitchcock's film "The Man Who Knew Too Much").  In reality the phrase is ungrammatical in Spanish, but the song was a great success, winning an Oscar for Livingston and Evans.